main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed and photographed in the Washington, D.C. area on April 8, 1952.
interesting points: The image was captured on a 20-minute time exposure, ruling out the possibility of it being a reflection or streaks of light.
The geologist who took the photo expressed confusion and was unable to arrive at a satisfactory explanation for the object.
The United States Air Force analyzed the negative but concluded that it did not indicate the existence of any unusual or unidentified aerial object.
The case involved the submission of a photograph to the Air Technical Intelligence Center for examination.
The official letter from the Air Force indicated that the image in question was likely caused by a slight distortion and did not represent an unidentified aerial object.
